I first tried Sweet & Sara products via the VeganEssentials website - the S'mores are outstanding!  The marshmallows are better than "regular" marshmallows, hands down - I don't care what they say about the freshness - these marshmallows have stayed in my refrigerator for MONTHS and still taste good.  Recently, I took advantage of a discount they offered through a group buying site and bought a few different items.  The hazelnut biscotti were delicious & crumbly (possibly from shipping) and were fantastic with my coffee.  They even sent me a sample - the strawberry marshmallow flavor is fantastic - it's not chemically or fake tasting like lots of fruit flavored sweets and I look forward to getting more.  They have great customer service and shipped everything very quickly!  Hurray for sweet treats!

My friend Anne and I were in the neighborhood and she had read some of the Yelp reviews on this place.  Naturally we had to try it.  We went in for lunch and were not disappointed. The staff is friendly without being too over the top and the food is delicious.  Someone said the portions were a little small but neither of us thought so.  The portions were perfect for us and for a lunch meal.  Anne had the Lasagna Bolognese and I tried the Fettuccine all' Amartriciana. My dish was home made fettucine combined with guanciale (pig cheek), pecorino cheese, onion, in a tomato sauce.  The sauce was slightly thickened with the cheese and was perfection.  It adhered to the pasta very well, and tasted like tomato, slightly tangy, and not overly sweet like some tomato sauce.  I also got to try Anne's lasagna and it was so much more than the standard fare you get elsewhere.  The bolognese sauce was meaty and thick, and the lasagna came in a little bowl.  The cheese on top must have been put under the broiler for a little bit because it has a crunchy, cheesy taste like no other lasagna I have ever had.  We each had a wonderful glass of wine and the owner brought us over tirimisu for desert, on the house.  I am not a fan of tirmisu because I don't like coffee but I had to give it a try anyway.  Do not pass this beautiful desert up if you have the chance to try it.  Even if you hate coffee you will love it. This place is definitely on my list of places to return to.
